00:31:31.147 --> 00:31:32.730
NICHOLAS KRISTOF:
People always think,

00:31:32.730 --> 00:31:37.030
because I spend a lot of time
covering genocide, and poverty,

00:31:37.030 --> 00:31:39.660
and sex trafficking,
that I must be

00:31:39.660 --> 00:31:45.360
kind of deeply depressed, and
greatly traumatized, and very

00:31:45.360 --> 00:31:45.860
fragile.

00:31:45.860 --> 00:31:49.890
And the truth is that, sure--
in reporting these things,

00:31:49.890 --> 00:31:52.380
you see some really
terrible things.

00:31:52.380 --> 00:31:54.497
But side by side with
the worst of humanity,

00:31:54.497 --> 00:31:55.830
you typically see the very best.

00:31:55.830 --> 00:31:59.550
You see incredible courage,
incredible resilience.

00:31:59.550 --> 00:32:01.510
You see people who are
making a difference

00:32:01.510 --> 00:32:04.030
and empowering people,
providing opportunity,

00:32:04.030 --> 00:32:07.470
and you also see an
element of progress.

00:32:07.470 --> 00:32:10.310
When I first-- and
I think this maybe

00:32:10.310 --> 00:32:12.110
is something that
we in journalism

00:32:12.110 --> 00:32:14.526
need to figure out better, how
to tell the story of-- when

00:32:14.526 --> 00:32:18.390
I first began traveling around
Africa as a backpacking law

00:32:18.390 --> 00:32:21.560
student, what really struck
me was the blindness.

00:32:21.560 --> 00:32:24.370
And there were so many
middle-aged people who,

00:32:24.370 --> 00:32:28.950
from river blindness, cataracts,
trachoma, could not see,

00:32:28.950 --> 00:32:32.050
could not work, could not
look after their kids.

00:32:32.050 --> 00:32:37.750
And for the book, we
talked to a woman in Mali

00:32:37.750 --> 00:32:41.150
who had had trachoma, which
is an incredibly painful way

00:32:41.150 --> 00:32:43.990
to go blind, for eight
years, had lost two kids

00:32:43.990 --> 00:32:46.230
because she couldn't
raise food for them.

00:32:46.230 --> 00:32:49.330
And then she got a $40
surgery through Helen Keller

00:32:49.330 --> 00:32:51.970
International, which is
right here in New York. $40

00:32:51.970 --> 00:32:56.680
surgery from a nurse,
20 minute operation.

00:32:56.680 --> 00:33:00.750
And then they're helping
her up off the table.

00:33:00.750 --> 00:33:02.560
And so, are you OK?

00:33:02.560 --> 00:33:04.560
Do you want us to walk
you back to your home?

00:33:04.560 --> 00:33:05.750
She says, get out of my way.

00:33:05.750 --> 00:33:06.760
I can see now.

00:33:06.760 --> 00:33:08.590
I can look after myself.

00:33:08.590 --> 00:33:10.900
$40-- I mean, that's
not depressing.

00:33:10.900 --> 00:33:14.920
That's inspiring,
what we can do.

00:33:14.920 --> 00:33:18.550
And on the whole,
that is happening.

00:33:18.550 --> 00:33:21.059
It's just not
happening fast enough.

00:33:21.059 --> 00:33:22.100
